  "name": "leios_withheld_fetch_at_quorum",
  "description": "EB-A (current_slot, hash=aa\u00d732) is offered and then receives 200 votes from 200 distinct voters across 20 batches \u2014 guaranteed to exceed any plausible quorum threshold. The node sends a MsgLeiosBlockRequest to fetch the body; the harness immediately disconnects without delivering a response. Under CIP-0164 the Leios voting pipeline requires a node to validate the EB body before including it in a certificate: a VT bundle certifies an EB whose content has been verified, not merely announced. A conforming node must not form a VT bundle for EB-A without having received and validated the body. The verifier should confirm that despite 200 valid votes, no VTBundleGenerated event is emitted for EB-A after the fetch disconnect.",
